---
import Layout from '../layouts/Layout.astro';

const lastUpdated = 'May 29, 2026';

const breadcrumbs = [
  { name: 'Home', url: '/' },
  { name: 'Terms of Use', url: '/terms/' },
];
---

<Layout
  title="Terms of Use — WrenchStack"
  description="The terms governing use of WrenchStack. Our content is independent editorial research provided for information only; do your own due diligence before buying."
  breadcrumbs={breadcrumbs}
>
  <article class="mx-auto max-w-3xl px-4 py-12">
    <header class="mb-8">
      <p class="mb-3 text-sm font-semibold uppercase tracking-wider text-orange-600">Legal</p>
      <h1 class="text-3xl font-bold tracking-tight text-slate-900 sm:text-4xl">Terms of Use</h1>
      <p class="mt-3 text-sm text-slate-500">Last updated: {lastUpdated}</p>
    </header>

    <section class="prose prose-slate max-w-none">
      <p>
        These Terms of Use govern your access to and use of WrenchStack (wrenchstack.com, the "Site"), an
        independent research publication operated by WrenchStack ("WrenchStack," "we," "us"). By using the
        Site, you agree to these terms. If you don't agree, please don't use the Site.
      </p>

      <h2>1. What WrenchStack is — and isn't</h2>
      <p>
        WrenchStack publishes independent editorial research, comparisons, and opinion about software and
        service vendors for trades and field-service businesses. Our content is provided for general
        informational purposes only. It is <strong>not</strong> professional, legal, financial, insurance, or
        accounting advice, and it is not a substitute for your own research. Before purchasing any product or
        service, verify current details directly with the vendor and consider your own circumstances.
      </p>

      <h2>2. Accuracy and "as is" availability</h2>
      <p>
        We work hard to keep information accurate and current — for example, we stamp pricing with a verified
        date — but vendor pricing, features, and terms change frequently and without notice to us. The Site and
        all content are provided "as is" and "as available," without warranties of any kind, express or implied,
        including accuracy, completeness, fitness for a particular purpose, or non-infringement. We do not
        warrant that the Site will be uninterrupted or error-free.
      </p>

      <h2>3. Affiliate relationships</h2>
      <p>
        WrenchStack earns affiliate commissions when readers sign up with some of the vendors we cover, via
        outbound links. This does not affect our editorial assessments: our <a href="/methodology/">WrenchStack
        Fit Score™ methodology</a> and our reputation flags are applied identically regardless of whether a
        vendor pays us. See our <a href="/disclosure/">Affiliate Disclosure</a> for details.
      </p>

      <h2>4. Third-party links and content</h2>
      <p>
        The Site links to third-party websites we don't operate or control. We're not responsible for the
        content, products, policies, or practices of those sites. Following an external link is at your own risk
        and subject to that site's own terms and privacy policy.
      </p>

      <h2>5. Intellectual property</h2>
      <p>
        The content, design, compilation, and original analysis on the Site — including the WrenchStack Fit
        Score™ name and methodology — are owned by WrenchStack and protected by intellectual-property laws.
        You may link to our pages and quote brief excerpts with attribution. You may not scrape, bulk-copy,
        republish, or create derivative works from substantial portions of the Site without our prior written
        permission. Vendor names and logos are the property of their respective owners and are used for
        identification and editorial purposes.
      </p>

      <h2>6. Acceptable use</h2>
      <p>You agree not to misuse the Site, including by attempting to disrupt it, accessing it through automated
        scraping that burdens our infrastructure, or using its content in ways that infringe our rights or
        mislead others about its source.</p>

      <h2>7. Limitation of liability</h2>
      <p>
        To the fullest extent permitted by law, WrenchStack and its operators will not be liable for any
        indirect, incidental, consequential, or special damages, or for any business, purchasing, or financial
        decision you make based on the Site. Your use of the Site and reliance on its content is at your own
        risk.
      </p>

      <h2>8. Changes to the Site and these terms</h2>
      <p>
        We may change, suspend, or discontinue any part of the Site, and we may update these terms from time to
        time. Material changes will be reflected in the "Last updated" date above. Continued use after a change
        means you accept the updated terms.
      </p>

      <h2>9. Governing law</h2>
      <p>
        These terms are governed by applicable law, without regard to conflict-of-laws principles. Where a
        specific jurisdiction is required, it will be the jurisdiction in which WrenchStack is operated. Nothing
        in these terms limits any non-waivable consumer rights you may have under your local law.
      </p>

      <h2>10. Contact</h2>
      <p>
        Questions about these terms? Email <a href="mailto:hello@wrenchstack.com">hello@wrenchstack.com</a>.
      </p>
    </section>
  </article>
</Layout>
